  "market_context": "USOIL trading on the daily timeframe with the previous month's high at 83.50 acting as resistance overhead and an unfilled weekly fair value gap sitting below near 78.50–79.50. Recent price action shows a swing high and swing low forming around these levels.",
  "key_observation": "A full-bodied up-close candle pushed into the previous month's high (point of interest); once price closed below it, that candle became a bearish order block that delivered price lower into the weekly FVG, then overlapping PD arrays at the discount supported a rally back to buy-side liquidity.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify HTF reference levels: previous month's high at 83.50 above and weekly fair value gap below, with a recent swing high and swing low marked.",
    "Observe a full-bodied up-close candle drive into the previous month's high point of interest.",
    "Wait for confirmation: a close below that up-close candle, turning it into a bearish order block; mark its opening price as resistance.",
    "Expect price to retest the order block opening and displace lower; price does retest and sells off, sweeping sell-side liquidity and creating a daily FVG.",
    "Track price reaching down into the weekly fair value gap, with the daily FVG supporting price on the way down.",
    "At the discount, identify the swept low as a POI and watch for a close over the high of the down-close candle to convert it into a bullish order block.",
    "On confirmation close, mark opening price as support; note overlapping PD arrays (bullish FVG plus order block) stacked at the same level.",
    "Price reaches into the order block, displaces out higher, and targets the buy-side liquidity at previous highs."
  ],
  "outcome": "Oil rallied higher from the overlapping bullish PD arrays and reached the previous highs (buy-side liquidity).",
  "lessons": "Full-bodied up-close candles into a POI become bearish order blocks when closed below (price delivers lower); down-close candles into a POI become bullish order blocks when closed above (price delivers higher). Overlapping PD arrays (FVG + OB) strengthen reaction zones.",
